CRUDZASO 

Project Overview

This project is a web-based TaskBoard management system developed as a frontend application using a simulated API with JSON Server.

It replicates a real-world ordering workflow where:

Users can register, log in, and place orders.

Administrators can manage products and supervise tasks.

The UI and layout are fully defined in Figma and must be followed exactly.

Project Scope
Included

Simulated authentication

Role-based access control (user / admin)

Fake API consumption with JSON Server

Task management

Admin dashboard with basic metrics

Session persistence

View separation by role

System Roles
Role Description
User: Client who creates, updates, and deletes tasks
Administrator: Manages tasks

Business rule: Users cannot access admin views, and admins do not access user views.

Technologies Used

HTML5

CSS3

Tailwind CSS

JavaScript (Vanilla)

JSON Server

SessionStorage

User Module

User registration (role assigned manual)

Login with credential validation

Task menu and button to create a new task

Users can view only their own task

Logout

Admin Module

Login with role detection

Access to admin dashboard

View metrics: every task

Security and Logic Rules

Protected routes based on session and role

Redirect to login if no active session

Users can only access their own data

Admins have access to all task

UI Design

Responsive layout

Required views:

Login

User task

User Create task

Admin admindashboard

Project Execution (Local)

Install dependencies:



npm install json-server

Start the fake API:

json-server --watch ./db/db.json 

Open the project with Live Server or a local server.